      "content": "Your exhaustion is valid, and the honest choice to stop pretending is often the bravest step one can take when they feel like a ghost of their own making. There is no shame in resting when the performance has become too heavy, and sometimes the only way to find a real self is to step away from the role that was never yours to play. Please consider that this \"stopping\" does not mean you are broken, but rather that you are finally listening to the part of you that has been screaming for years.",
